WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:08.400
 Pair the miniTek with your mobile phone 

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:25.600
 Activate the Bluetooth® feature on your phone. For most mobile phones, this option is available under Settings. 

00:00:25.700 --> 00:00:35.600
 Turn on miniTek ™. 

00:00:35.700 --> 00:00:39.200
 Press and hold the "Phone" button for 5 seconds. 

00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:48.200
 The “phone” button and the audio source button will then blink once and the “phone” button will continue to flash. 

00:00:48.300 --> 00:00:51.100
 It is now in device pairing mode. 

00:00:51.200 --> 00:00:58.100
 Activate the search on your phone to search for Bluetooth devices. 

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:02.800
 Select the RCU on your phone. 

00:01:02.900 --> 00:01:10.000
 Your phone was successfully paired with miniTec. 

00:01:13.700 --> 00:01:19.000
 You will hear the ringtone in your device. 

00:01:19.100 --> 00:01:26.800
 To answer the call, please press the "Phone" button once. 

00:01:26.900 --> 00:01:33.500
 To cancel the call, press the "Phone" button again. 

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:41.200
 You will hear the ring of the phone ring. 

00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:52.300
 If you do not want to answer the call, press the "Phone" button twice. 

00:01:56.400 --> 00:02:00.800
 Use the transmitter for a TV 

00:02:05.100 --> 00:02:10.100
 Find the cables you need to connect to the TV. 

00:02:12.600 --> 00:02:17.100
 Find the audio output on your TV. Connect the red and white connectors to the audio outputs. 

00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:29.100
 Turn on the transmitter. 

00:02:31.200 --> 00:02:39.200
 Press the audio source button to receive the transmitted signal. 

00:02:39.300 --> 00:02:43.000
 Then the miniTeken button is the audio source, and the indicator light on the transmitter flashes blue… 

00:02:43.100 --> 00:02:46.600
 ... as long as the signal is not received. 

00:02:46.700 --> 00:02:52.000
 At this point, both lights light continuously blue, indicating that the signal transmission is in progress. 

00:02:52.100 --> 00:02:56.400
 If you need to increase or decrease the volume, adjust it… 

00:02:56.500 --> 00:02:59.200
 ... using the volume button on the transmitter. There are 5 setup options. 

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:08.700
 Adjust the volume to a smaller setting using the miniTek. 

00:03:08.800 --> 00:03:14.700
 If you want to mute the environmental microphones and only want to hear the signal from the TV, 

00:03:14.800 --> 00:03:18.800
 ... press the "Mute" button at the top of the miniTek. 

00:03:18.900 --> 00:03:27.600
 To stop transmission, press the “P” button on the miniTeken to return to normal hearing aid function. 

